Vice President Mike Pence spoke with Trey Ware on the Stephens Roofing Newsmaker Hotline about the federal government's response to Hurricane Harvey. Pence praised the efforts of local officials and first responders in Texas and emphasized the importance of listening to their instructions. He mentioned that the federal government has deployed thousands of officials and resources to support rescue efforts. Pence also mentioned that disaster assistance and resources for recovery will be available once the flood waters recede. He confirmed that President Trump and the First Lady plan to visit the affected areas in Texas. Pence urged listeners to continue to follow the guidance of local officials and emphasized that the storm is still dangerous. The Vice President expressed solidarity and support for the people of Texas, and thanked Trey Ware for his efforts in helping the affected areas.